| publisher = Laboratory of Wound Healing and Cell Biology, Burns Institute, 304th Clinical Department, General Hospital of PLA, Beijing 100037, China.
| quote = In hypertrophic scar tissue, no sweet gland and hair follicle exist usually because of the dermal and epidermal damage in extensive thermal skin injury, thus imparing regulation of body temperature.
