  | title = New mechanical insights into wound healing and scar tissue formation
  | quote = The matrix grows stiffer and, at a certain point, the fibroblasts stop migrating and, like Popeye, change into powerful contractile cells, anchoring themselves to the matrix and pulling the edges of the wound together.
