| quote = Studies in sheep have indicated that myofibroblasts are absent in early scarless fetal wounds but are present during healing at later stages when prominent scarring occurs. In addition, incisional or small excisional wounds (2 mm) heal without a scar and do not contain myofibroblasts. In contrast, larger excisional wounds that heal with a scar contain strong a-SMA staining, with the number of myofibroblasts correlating with the size of the wound and amount of scarring.   | publisher = o-wm.com
  | date = 2008-03-09
  | url = http://www.o-wm.com/content/regenerative-healing-fetal-skin-a-review-literature?page=0,11
