| quote = myofibroblasts become differentiated from other cells in the wound within a few days after the onset of healing, and in the rat model can reach a peak where about 70% of the fibroblastic cells present are of the myofibroblast phenotype. | publisher = freepatentsonline.com | date = | url = http://www.freepatentsonline.com/y2005/0054608.html| accessdate = 2010-03-26}}</ref> and is responsible for fibrosis on tissue.<ref name=Leask201103>{{Cite web
